    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Louis</placeName> <date>October 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1853&#47;5604</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Pha</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">With great pleasure I acknowledge<lb/> the receipt of your favor of the <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> <add>&#63;</add> and thank you for<lb/> the kind inquiries and friendly wishes concerning my<lb/> father. He arrived last spring safely in <placeName>New York</placeName> and<lb/> I met him there we sold parts of the Books he had brought<lb/> with him though at a sacrifice to some <placeName>N. Y.</placeName> hebrew Book<lb/> sellers. This kept us so long there that I had to forego the pleasure<lb/> of visiting you in <placeName>Pha</placeName>. And to return the shortest route to this<lb/> city&#44; where I established since a pretty large Hardware<lb/> Business. The opening of this new business deprived me of all<lb/> <sic>leasure</sic> either to write you and for your monthly&#44; or to get<lb/> you any subscribers. The latter is moreover a very difficult<lb/> thing&#44; our correligionaries being either too indifferent or perhaps<lb/> too poor to pay for it. Of the two subscribers which you<lb/> mention the one &#40;<persName>Mr. Nuttenwieser</persName>&#41; is as you justly suppose<lb/> either in <placeName>California</placeName> or <placeName>Europe</placeName>&#44; or may be <sic>pedling</sic> among the<lb/> Indians&#59; and the second &#40;<persName>Mr Block</persName>&#41; is among the blessed<lb/> that have changed this life for a more perfect one.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I enclose herewith &#36;5.00&#44; which I hope you will<lb/> accept as payment in full for the one copy which I receive</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I will try to get&#8212;if possible&#8212;payments from the heirs of<lb/> <persName>Mr Block</persName> and send you the amount as soon as received.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">You have the kindness to ask my views on your<lb/> changing the Occident into a weekly paper. I believe that<lb/> most of your subscribers will be pleased with such a change<lb/> and you will probably get some new subscribers by it&#44; besides<lb/> you would get more <hi rend="underline">advertisements</hi>&#44; the greatest aid for<lb/> every periodical&#59; but I doubt that it would even then<lb/> prove a profitable speculation.</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>In my opinion&#8212;which may altogether<lb/> wrong&#8212;you could succeed if your paper becomes the<lb/> exponent of the sentiments and views of the majority of<lb/> our people here&#44; if it adapts itself to the <add>&#63;</add> of <hi rend="underline">our</hi><lb/> times&#44; if it was a paper for <hi rend="underline">American</hi> Jews&#59;</p>
			<p>As an advocate of the Jews of the middle age&#44; of absolute<lb/> views and customs&#44; of sentiments that exist but in very few<lb/> &#40;and among these few mostly such as your <sic>orthodoxie</sic> will not deem<lb/> sufficient it will receive but little support&#41;.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">There are among those who support your paper certainly<lb/> many that differ widely with its views and tendency&#8212;but<lb/> <hi rend="underline">like it</hi> for its undisputed great merits&#44; for the many excellent<lb/> pages it contains for the high esteem which they bear to<lb/> it able conductor notwithstanding this difference of opinions<lb/> and sentiments in many points.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I hope you will excuse the frankness with which<lb/> I give you my unpretending opinion</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">and will accept with friendly feelings</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">my best wishes to the next year</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">and the assurance of</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">my respect &#38; affection&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">with which I remain yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Isidor Bush</persName></p>
          
        </body>
    </text>
